evaluate


public abstract PolicyFailure[] evaluate(
Evaluate current check in provided as PolicyContext object

 
This method is called in background thread, so user interaction should be made using SwingUtilities.invokeAndWait(Runnable).
 If evaluation is long running it is recommended to call com.intellij.openapi.progress.ProgressIndicator#checkCanceled()
 to give user a chance to cancel. Prior to evaluation #loadState(org.jdom.Element) is called. Runtime exception thrown out of this method
 will be reported as evaluation error.






Parameters:
policycontext - configuration of check in to evaluate
progressIndicator - progress indicator

Returns:
collection is evaluation errors or empty array if check in is OK to be done









canEdit


public abstract boolean canEdit()




Check if current policy supports configuring with UI. If yes, Edit button for the policy will be enabled in Edit Chec In Policies dialog






Returns:
true if current policy configuration can be changed










edit


public abstract boolean edit(Project project)




Open edit dialog for the policy

 
Called in UI thread if canEdit() returned true. #loadState(org.jdom.Element) is called in before the call.
 If method returns true, #saveState(org.jdom.Element) is called afterwards





Parameters:
project - current project

Returns:
true if edit was done successfully and policy state changed










loadState


public abstract void loadState(
Load policy configuration state from org.jdom.Element node. Runtime exception thrown out of this method
 will be reported as loading error.





Parameters:
element - root element of the configuration XML store









saveState


public abstract void saveState(
Save policy configuration state to org.jdom.Element node. Runtime exception thrown out of this method
 will be reported as saving error.





Parameters:
element - root element of the configuration XML store









activate


public void activate(
This method is invoked when user double clicks on policy failure item in Checkin Parameters dialog.
 Default implementation shows message dialog with the problem description





Parameters:
project - project for the current frame
policyFailure - item that is activated
